{"id":3592,"date":"2021-10-29T13:17:00","date_gmt":"2021-10-29T12:17:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/saltinourhair.com\/?p=3592"},"modified":"2022-06-21T15:27:01","modified_gmt":"2022-06-21T13:27:01","slug":"chefchaouen-morocco","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/morocco\/chefchaouen-morocco\/","title":{"rendered":"9 Best Things To Do In Chefchaouen, Morocco"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"todo\">1. Wander the Blue Streets<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The number one reason to visit Chefchaouen is for its beautiful streets, filled with houses painted a variety of blues. There are many theories as to why the walls are blue. Some say it&#x2019;s for practical reasons, such as keeping mosquitoes away or keeping the houses cooler.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/23115407\/chefcaouen-morocco-540x810.jpg\" alt=\"chefcaouen morocco\"><\/noscript><img width=\"225\" height=\"338\" alt=\"chefcaouen morocco\" class=\"wp-image-32102 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/23115407\/chefcaouen-morocco-540x810.jpg 540w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/23115407\/chefcaouen-morocco-300x450.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/23115407\/chefcaouen-morocco-600x900.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/23115407\/chefcaouen-morocco-400x600.jpg 400w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/03\/23115407\/chefcaouen-morocco-225x338.jpg 225w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\